research_municipality_step.notes: Seattle operates under a mayor-council government. Katie Wilson assumed the role of Mayor on January 1, 2026. The City Council consists of nine members, with seven elected by district and two at-large. Joy Hollingsworth was elected Council President in early 2026. Eddie Lin was elected in November 2025 to an unexpired term. Debora Juarez was appointed in July 2025 and will serve until a special election in 2026. Alexis Mercedes Rinck and Dionne Foster are at-large council members.
